Detailed Description

Listener for Search events. The abstract functions are the callback functions that is called for the respective asynchronous function call in SearchInterface.

Create a subclass and implement the callbacks and add a subclass object to the SearchInterface to start getting search callbacks.

The error function, declared in the super class Listener, will be called for all requests that returns with an error.

Member Enumeration Documentation

enum WFAPI::SearchListener::ImageStatus

This enum describes different statuses for image sets. It is used in the ...ImageStatusUpdated callback functions.

Enumerator:
CURRENT_IMAGES_OK  The current images are ok to be used.
CURRENT_IMAGES_NOT_OK  The current images are not ok and will be deleted.
UPDATED_IMAGES_OK  The images have been updated and are ok to use.

virtual void WFAPI::SearchListener::categoryTreeReceived ( RequestID  requestID,
bool  treeUpdated 
) [inline, virtual]

A reply to the category tree update request. This does not necesarily mean that the category tree has been updated since there might not be any other category tree for the coordinates supplied in the request.

Parameters:
requestID The identification of the category tree request sent from the SearchInterface.
treeUpdated If this is true it means that we have received an updated version of the category tree. False if the category tree is up to date.
